<paragraph id="8B870F6D657B862CFF4CDB7CFD81FCA0" blockId="7.[151,1436,815,1310]" box="[151,626,815,842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFF4CDB7CFEBDFCA0" bold="true" box="[151,334,815,842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Common name</emphasis>
. ‘Fine delicate lacewing’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3225CE6657B862CFF1CDB00FB4FFBAC" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B870F6D657B862CFF1CDB00FB4FFBAC" blockId="7.[151,1436,815,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFF1CDB00FEB1FC84" bold="true" box="[199,322,851,878]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing with few small irregular markings midway along inner and middle gradate series; hind wing with larger ovoid spot midway along inner gradate series and smaller spot on cross-vein further along gradate series, darker venation and faint suffusion in end-twigging marginally along the posterior part of hind wing; both wings with three gradate series; forewing RA with RA-RP cross-veins simple, lacking interconnecting cross-veins; basal half of forewing with irregular cross-veins connecting RP branches; inner-most gradate series of hind wing sharply curved anteriorly at midpoint in a distinct sigmoid shape; hind wing with distinct ovoid marking midway along inner gradate series; end-twigging present along most of posterior margin of both wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3225CE6657B862CFF1CDC1CFB49FAF4" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B870F6D657B862CFF1CDC1CFB49FAF4" blockId="7.[151,1436,815,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFF1CDC1CFEBBFB80" bold="true" box="[199,328,1103,1130]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFE8CDC03FDC2FB80" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[343,561,1104,1130]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptalea">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFE8CDC03FDC2FB80" box="[343,561,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Apochrysa leptalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the group of Afrotropical species characterised by a hind wing with the inner-most gradate series arranged in a sigmoid shape with a distinct ovoid marking mid way along the gradates, and the posterodistal margin having suffuse infuscate shading. These characters, along with the presence of three gradate series in both wings differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFDAEDCEFFD1CFB3C" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[629,751,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptalea">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFDAEDCEFFD1CFB3C" box="[629,751,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">A. leptalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFCADDCEFFC1DFB3C" authorityName="Schneider" authorityYear="1851" box="[886,1006,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFCADDCEFFC1DFB3C" box="[886,1006,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Apochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFB8FDCEFFADDFB3C" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1108,1326,1212,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptalea">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFB8FDCEFFADDFB3C" box="[1108,1326,1212,1238]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Apochrysa leptalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from southern 
<collectingCountry id="F32F4FFD657B862CFEE6DCB3FE3CFB10" box="[317,463,1248,1274]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="5483B1CF657B862CFDD7DCB3FD9DFB10" box="[524,622,1248,1274]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFD4FDCB3FCE2FB10" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[660,785,1248,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptalea">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFD4FDCB3FCE2FB10" box="[660,785,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">H. leptalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is housed in the Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique—Bruxelles. The type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE657B862CFDC2DD57FD72FAF7" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1912" box="[537,641,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Osmylidae" genus="Osmylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picteti">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F657B862CFDC2DD57FD72FAF7" box="[537,641,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">O. picteti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed by Navás as “ 
<collectingRegion id="49FCC18F657B862CFCA5DD57FC4FFAF4" box="[894,956,1284,1310]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Cabo</collectingRegion>
de Buena Esperanza”.
</paragraph>
